Everything seems to be alright until I created a new ```@SpringBootTest``` class. Some tests beging to fail because the embedded Tomcat could not be started (error message: ```Address already in use```). So I put on my bath cap and dove into the deep abyusse of my code and its dependencies to find out why Tomcat is using an address which is already used.

The first thing I found out was that Tomcat is listening on two ports: ```8080``` and a random port, see the following log:
```
