I was confused, why is Tomcat listening on its default port ```8080```. 

After some trial and error with the Spring Boot annotations and configurations I found the culprit. The ```@PostConstruct``` method causes Tomcat to listening on port ```8080```. 

For me it seems that the injected ```WebServerApplicationContext``` doesn&#39;t references a *listening* tomcat instance and would create a new ```Connector``` instance with the default port when ``` webServerAppCtxt.getWebServer().getPort()``` is called in the ```@PostConstruct``` method. Why does it behave like this?

A working example can be found [here][1]. Simple checkout and build it with maven or your prefered IDE. The example test will fail if Tomcat is listening on the default port ```8080```.


